This paper is primarily focused on improving search ranking quality, which falls under the category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses click models, which are commonly used in Natural Language Processing (NLP) and Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). The proposed search intent bias hypothesis involves machine learning techniques, which are often used in the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses biases in data, which can be relevant to the sub-category of Cybersecurity (cs.CY) and the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
